    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-01-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-01-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="26"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d26">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 611.3231/185.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Petropolis</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-01-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 2, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Executive is authorized to grant during 1911, 30 per cent reduction in the
                    duty on flour and 20 per cent on one or more other articles of American
                    production.</p>
                <p>Parcel post and arbitration conventions with the United States ratified by
                    Congress December 30. Exchange of the ratifications of the former here
                    awaited.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dudley.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
